00037     bool string2float(const std::string& s, float &v){
00038         if(s==RDK_INF_STRING) { v = RDK_INF32; return true; } 
00039         if(s==RDK_NAN_STRING) { v = RDK_NAN; return true; } 
00040         return 1 == sscanf(s.c_str(), "%f", &v);
00041     }

00080 void regression(
00081     const std::vector<Point2d>& points, double&theta, double&rho, double&error) {
00082     int n = points.size(); assert(n);
00083     double mu_x = 0;
00084     double mu_y = 0;
00085     for(int a=0;a<n;a++) {
00086         mu_x += points[a].x / n;
00087         mu_y += points[a].y / n;
00088     }
00089     double s_x2 = 0;
00090     double s_y2 = 0;
00091     double s_xy = 0;
00092     for(int a=0;a<n;a++) {
00093         s_x2 += square(points[a].x-mu_x);
00094         s_y2 += square(points[a].y-mu_y);
00095         s_xy += (points[a].y-mu_y)*(points[a].x-mu_x);
00096     }
00097     
00098     theta = 0.5 * atan2(-2*s_xy, s_y2-s_x2);
00099     rho = mu_x * cos(theta) + mu_y * sin(theta);
00100     if(rho>0) {
00101         rho = - rho;
00102         theta = theta + M_PI;
00103     }
00104     error = 0;
00105 }

00109     bool parseMatrix(
00110         const vector<string>& sv, int start_index, int rows, int columns,
00111         DMatrix<double> &m, string*error) {
00112         assert(rows>=1);
00113         assert(columns>=1);
00114         
00115         m = DMatrixD(rows, columns);
00116         
00117         for(int i=0;i<rows;i++)
00118         for(int j=0;j<columns;j++) {
00119             std::string token = sv[start_index + i*columns +j];
00120             if(!RDK2::TextUtils::parse<double>(token, m[i][j])) {
00121                 if(error) *error = std::string(
00122                     "While reading matrix element i,j=") + toString(i) +"," + toString(j)
00123                  + "Could not parse token '"+ token+"'.";
00124                 return false;
00125             }
00126         }
00127         return true;
00128     }

00130     bool parsePoint(
00131         const string& sx, const string& sy, const string& stheta,
00132         Point2od& p, std::string*error) {
00133 
00134         if( !RDK2::TextUtils::parse(sx, p.x) ||
00135                 !RDK2::TextUtils::parse(sy, p.y) ||
00136         !RDK2::TextUtils::parse(stheta, p.theta)) {
00137                 if(error) *error = string("Could not parse point from: ") + sx + "; "
00138                         + sy + "; "+stheta;
00139                 return false;
00140         }
00141 
00142         return true;
